---
description: Use n8n-as-code TypeScript workflow files and explicit sync discipline for n8n workflow work.
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "**/*.workflow.ts"
---

When editing an n8n workflow file:

- Treat `.workflow.ts` as the source of truth.
- Keep the TypeScript decorator structure with `@workflow`, `@node`, and `@links`.
- Preserve the `<workflow-map>` block at the top of the file.
- Pull the workflow from n8n before editing when the workspace is initialized.
- Push the workflow back after editing.
- Use exact node schema information from `n8nac skills node-info <nodeName>` or the equivalent MCP tool.
- Never invent node parameters, connection types, or credential fields.
- Regular node connections use `.out(0).to(target.in(0))`.
- AI sub-node connections use `.uses()`.
- `ai_tool` and `ai_document` values are arrays; most other AI connections are single refs.
